        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "A rather foppish artist, Embraced when your sire was captivated by your paintings. You are a good painter, sculptor, musician, speaker, and gnerally skilled artistic dilettante. You come from the Pyreneese courts... That is your cover at least. You are a serial killer who seeks to capture the ultimate agony in sculpture. The worst part of your passion is that the medium you are fascinated with (marble) is so stable, and the model you work from is so weak (flesh). You may have to discover a way to break the wall blocking your studies of flesh and bone, and start to sculpt entire creatures into beautiful beings. You are one of the Volgirre that left the Sabbat and came to the Camarilla. You did not focus on the rites of the sect, and over the years you have felt your bonds of Vaulderie fade. The Camarilla has many merits, such as being able to focus on art vs if your pack mate wants your Blood. But there are many skills the Sabbat have that should not be lost. You see yourself as a man to unite the clans, if not all vampires. Your last court of Marseilles, you had many Sabbat friends. But the relationships gradually came to light. Other Volgirre recommended you go to a battleground city, so the rules would not be as strict as a classic European city. You traveled slowly, exploring city by city when you heard the call to come to Los Angeles by the Justicars. It seemed like a great opportunity to learn while getting a good reputation. You are not a traitor, but you are very sympathetic to the Sabbat cause"
        ],
        [
